wikipedia_page.main: Lieutenant James Cromwell Bush  (1 March 1891 – 7 October 1917) was a British World War I flying ace credited with six aerial victories.

response: * Lt James Bush M.C. (1891–1917), World War I flying ace

* James Bush (actor) (1907–1987), actor in American films of the 1930s and 1940s
